author: NetBrain
description:
Device Type:
Alcatel OmniSwitch
Command:
show ip isis status

samples.content:
-> show isis status
==========================================================
ISIS Status
==========================================================
System Id : 0050.0500.5001
Admin State                 : UP
Protocols Enabled           : IPv4, IPv6
Last Enabled                : WED OCT 24 10:05:55 2007
Level Capability            : L1L2
Authentication Check        : True
Authentication Type         : None
Graceful Restart            : Disabled
GR helper-mode              : Disabled
LSP Lifetime                : 1200
LSP Wait                    : Max :5 sec, Initial :0 sec, Second :1 sec
Adjacency Check             : Loose
L1 Auth Type                : None
L2 Auth Type                : None
L1 Wide Metrics-only        : Disabled
L2 Wide Metrics-only        : Disabled
L1 LSDB Overload            : Disabled
L2 LSDB Overload            : Disabled
L1 LSPs                     : 177
L2 LSPs                     : 177
Last SPF                    : FRI OCT 26 05:04:09 2007
SPF Wait                    : Max :10000 ms, Initial :1000 ms, Second :1000 ms
Hello-Auth Check            : Enabled
Csnp-Auth Check             : Enabled
Psnp-Auth Check             : Enabled
L1 Hello-Auth Check         : Enabled
L1 Csnp-Auth Check          : Enabled
L1 Psnp-Auth Check          : Enabled
L2 Hello-Auth Check         : Enabled
L2 Csnp-Auth Check          : Enabled
L2 Psnp-Auth Check          : Enabled
Multi-topology              : Enabled
Area Address                : 49.0000
===========================================================

variables.desc: The system ID of the router. The system ID is a fixed size, six octet field in the NSAP. In an IS-IS routing domain, each router is identified by a 6-octet hexadecimal system ID.
variables.name: $system_id

variables.desc: The state of the router (Up or Down).
variables.name: $admin_state

variables.desc: The protocol enabled on the router: IPv4 or IPv6
variables.name: $protocol_enable

variables.desc: The date and time when the router is enabled.
variables.name: $last_enable

variables.desc: The level capability of the router (L1, L2, or L1L2).
variables.name: $level_cap

variables.desc: Indicates the status of the authentication (true or false).
variables.name: $authen_check

variables.desc: The type of authentication (password or md5).
variables.name: $authen_type

variables.desc: Indicates if graceful restart is Enabled or Disabled.
variables.name: $graceful_restart

variables.desc: Indicates if the helper mode of graceful restart is Enabled or Disabled.
variables.name: $gr_helper_mode

variables.desc: The Lifetime of the LSP (in seconds).

variables.desc: The Wait time of the LSP (in seconds).

variables.desc: The Wait time of the LSP (in seconds).
variables.name: $lsp_wait_init

variables.desc: The Wait time of the LSP (in seconds).
variables.name: $lsp_wait_second

variables.desc: The adjacency check configuration on the router

variables.desc: The authentication type (password or md5) for Level-1 adjacency.
variables.name: $l1_auth_type

variables.desc: The authentication type (password or md5) for Level-2 adjacency.
variables.name: $l2_auth_type

variables.desc: Indicates whether wide metrics is Enabled or Disabled for Level-1 adjacency.

variables.desc: Indicates whether wide metrics is Enabled or Disabled for Level-2 adjacency.

variables.desc: Indicates whether LSDB Overload is Enabled or Disabled for Level-1 adjacency.
variables.name: $l1_lsdb_overload

variables.desc: Indicates whether LSDB Overload is Enabled or Disabled for Level-2 adjacency.
variables.name: $l2_lsdb_overload

variables.desc: The number of LSPs for Level-1 adjacency.
variables.name: $l1_lsp

variables.desc: The number of LSPs for Level-2 adjacency.
variables.name: $l2_lsp

variables.desc: The date and duration of the last SPF calculation.
variables.name: $last_spf

variables.desc: The Wait time for the SPF calculation.
variables.name: $spf_wait_max

variables.desc: The Wait time for the SPF calculation.
variables.name: $spf_wait_initial

variables.desc: The Wait time for the SPF calculation.
variables.name: $spf_wait_second

variables.desc: Indicates the status of hello authentication check (Enabled or Disabled).
variables.name: $hello_auth_check

variables.desc: Indicates the status of global CSNP authentication check (Enabled or Disabled).
variables.name: $csnp_auth_check

variables.desc: Indicates the status of global PSNP authentication check (Enabled or Disabled).
